ainst the state. This book not only challenges theories in the study of citizenship but also the axioms of integration in Western social sciences in general.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Nov 2022) 0aCentral-local government relationszGeorgia (Republic) 0aCentral-local government relationszGeorgia (Republic). 0aCitizenshipzGeorgia (Republic)zTʻušetʻi. 0aCitizenshipzGeorgia (Republic)zTʻušetʻi. 0aCitizenshipzGeorgia (Republic)zTʿušetʿi. 0aGovernment, Resistance tozGeorgia (Republic)zTʻušetʻi. 0aGovernment, Resistance tozGeorgia (Republic)zTʻušetʻi. 0aGovernment, Resistance tozGeorgia (Republic)zTʿušetʿi. 0aPost-communismzGeorgia (Republic)zTʻušetʻi. 0aPost-communismzGeorgia (Republic)zTʻušetʻi. 0aPost-communismzGeorgia (Republic)zTʿušetʿi. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBerghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311099823840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978178238297340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781782382973423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781782382973/original  a978-3-11-099823-8  Berghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK